Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {Shifting cultivation is a traditional farming system that has been
   practised in many parts of the world for centuries. It is rampant in the
   northeast region of India and has widespread environmental and
   socio-economic impacts. The application of geospatial technology for
   studying the same has been slowly but surely gaining momentum. This
