   quantifying areas and rates of soil erosion for the development of
   better soil conservation plans. The resultant map of annual soil erosion
   shows a maximum soil loss of 14.917 t h(-1) year(-1) and the
   computations suggest that about only 5.76\% (1,184 hectares) of the area
   comes under the severe soil erosion zone followed by the high-erosion
   zone (11.50\% of the total area). The dominant high soil erosion areas
   are located in the central and southern portion of the watershed and it
   is attributed to the shifting cultivation, and forest degradation along
   with the combined effect of K, LS and C factor. The RUSLE model in
   combination with GIS and remote sensing techniques also enables the
