Month = {MAY},
Abstract = {The article discusses the phased development of the Hainan Special
   Economic Zone (SEZ) from 1988 to 2022. It examines the transformation of
   Hainan's economy from a region with traditional agriculture to its
   development into an international tourist island and center of
   international trade. The successful development of the Hainan SEZ is
   explained by the approach to establishing the special economic zone and
   the specifics of policy implementation. In China, SEZs were created for
   an indefinite period in regions with distinct competitive advantages for
   both territorial development and economic sectors simultaneously. The
   authors see the peculiarities of policy implementation in the phased
   establishment of a special economic and legal regime, which includes the
   introduction and improvement of stimulating tools and incentive
   mechanisms in the areas of attracting foreign investment, customs
   duties, land relations, tax incentives, the introduction of a visa-free
   regime, duty-free trade, and the enhancement of administrative measures
   in accordance with changing goals and objectives. The factors
   contributing to the success of the Hainan SEZ include ensuring the
   steady development of infrastructure as the basis for structural shifts
   in the region's economy; the introduction of international standards in
   hotel services and environmental management; the improvement of
   intellectual property protection mechanisms; the creation of intelligent
   logistics systems based on automation and artificial intelligence
   technologies; optimization of customs control; improvement of
   international payment methods using the yuan; and the provision of
   various financial services. The peculiarities of policy implementation
   and the factors influencing the development of the Hainan SEZ create a
   synergistic effect, providing favorable conditions for business
   activities and offering high-quality goods and services for consumers.
   All of this contributes to economic growth and the improvement of the
   living standards of the population in the Hainan region and China as a
   whole. China's experience in ensuring the effective functioning of SEZs
   and the development of the regions they are located in can serve as a
   basis for improving approaches to the creation and operation of SEZs in
